para_trans: Regarding administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report (DPR) submitted by the local bodies for the works to be taken up out of the prize money received under Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0.
Chincholi Gurav Gram Panchayat.
Government of Maharashtra
Department of Environment and Climate Change
Government Decision No: Mission-2024 / Q. No.04 (29) / T.C.19
Martyr Rajguru Chowk, Madam Cama Marg,
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032
Date: May 23, 2025

Read: (1) Government Decision, Environment and Climate Change Department No. Mission - 2024 / Q. No.66 / T. 1 dated 27th September, 2024 (2) Government Decision, Environment and Climate Change Department No. Abhiyaan-2021 / P.S. No.57 / T. No.1, dated 8th February, 2022 (3) The minutes of the meeting of the Committee constituted for the approval of the Administrator dated 02nd May, 2025

Preamble: The procedure for the award of cash and appropriation of the prize money to the winning local bodies in the 12 groups of Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 has been notified vide Government Decision dated 27.09.2024 at Reference No. Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meeting held on 02.05.2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to grant administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.
The government's decision:

Considering the points mentioned in the introduction, the total amount received by Chincholi Gurav Gram Panchayat under My Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 is Rs. 15.00 The focus will be on the works to be undertaken out of the prize money of Rs. The Detailed Project Report costing ₹15,00, 000.00 (Rupees Fifteen Lakhs only) has been submitted by the Village Development Officer, Chincholi Gurav Gram Panchayat with the technical approval of the Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad Ahilyanagar. The proposal was submitted by Chincholi Gurav Gram Panchayat. Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change
Page 1 of 4
Government Decision No: Mission-2024 / Q.No.04 / T.H.2, dated: 23rd May, 2025

The date of the committee constituted under his chairmanship was taken into consideration in its meetings held on 02nd May, 2025. As per the recommendation made by the said committee, the total amount submitted by Chincholi Gurav Gram Panchayat is Rs. The works in the Detailed Project Report costing ₹15,00, 000.00 (Rupees Fifteen Lakhs only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions and conditions. The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-9.
2. Terms and Conditions 1) The working mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report shall be the Chincholi Gurav Gram Panchayat.

2) The financial and physical progress report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the date of approval by the Administrator.
4) If the amount of the prize exceeds the amount, it should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.

3. Under the Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan, Chincholi Gurav Gram Panchayat has bagged the 3rd position at Nashik Zonal level in the "Gram Panchayat Group (2. 0 thousand to 5. 0 thousand population)" category with a prize money of Rs. Out of the prize money of Rs. The first instalment of ₹7.5 lakh has been disbursed to them. Since the detailed project report of the works to be taken out of this prize money has been granted administrative approval by the Government as per paragraph-1 above, the remaining amount of the prize money to Chincholi Gurav Gram Panchayat is Rs. The government is approving the disbursement of the second instalment of ₹7.50 lakh (only) through the Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
The Government decision is available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
